National Transportation Safety Board
Aviation Accident Final Report
Location: Canton, IL
Accident Number: CHI06CA025
Date & Time: 11/02/2005, 1045 CST
Registration: N9664D
Aircraft: Piper PA22-150
Aircraft Damage: Destroyed
Defining Event:
Injuries: 1 Minor
Flight Conducted Under: Part 91: General Aviation - Personal
 Analysis The airplane was destroyed by fire after an emergency landing due to an in-flight fire.
The pilot said that after taking off and executing a left hand traffic pattern departure, he noticed smoke emanating from the left side of the instrument panel.
An emergency landing was executed and the airplane rolled to a stop on the grass adjacent to the runway.
The airplane was consumed by the fire after the pilot had exited the airplane.
Postaccident examination of the airplane failed to reveal evidence of the original source of the fire.
Probable Cause and Findings The National Transportation Safety Board determines the probable cause(s) of this accident to be: The fire for undetermined reasons.
Findings Occurrence #1: FIRE Phase of Operation: CLIMB - TO CRUISE Findings 1.
